  17 if IS_TYPE_CHECKING:
  18     from typing import (

  34 class DotEnv():
  35 
  36     def __init__(self, dotenv_path, verbose=False, encoding=None):
  37         # type: (Union[Text, _PathLike, _StringIO], bool, Union[None, Text]) -> None
  38         self.dotenv_path = dotenv_path  # type: Union[Text,_PathLike, _StringIO]
  39         self._dict = None  # type: Optional[Dict[Text, Text]]
  40         self.verbose = verbose  # type: bool
  41         self.encoding = encoding  # type: Union[None, Text]
  42 
  43     @contextmanager
  44     def _get_stream(self):
  45         # type: () -> Iterator[IO[Text]]
  46         if isinstance(self.dotenv_path, StringIO):
  47             yield self.dotenv_path
  48         elif os.path.isfile(self.dotenv_path):
  49             with io.open(self.dotenv_path, encoding=self.encoding) as stream:
  50                 yield stream
  51         else:
  52             if self.verbose:
  53                 warnings.warn("File doesn't exist {}".format(self.dotenv_path))  # type: ignore
  54             yield StringIO('')
  55 
  56     def dict(self):
  57         # type: () -> Dict[Text, Text]
  58         """Return dotenv as dict"""
  59         if self._dict:
  60             return self._dict
  61 
  62         values = OrderedDict(self.parse())
  63         self._dict = resolve_nested_variables(values)
  64         return self._dict
  65 
  66     def parse(self):
  67         # type: () -> Iterator[Tuple[Text, Text]]
  68         with self._get_stream() as stream:
  69             for mapping in parse_stream(stream):
  70                 if mapping.key is not None and mapping.value is not None:
  71                     yield mapping.key, mapping.value
  72 
  73     def set_as_environment_variables(self, override=False):
  74         # type: (bool) -> bool
  75         """
  76         Load the current dotenv as system environemt variable.
  77         """
  78         for k, v in self.dict().items():
  79             if k in os.environ and not override:
  80                 continue
  81             os.environ[to_env(k)] = to_env(v)
  82 
  83         return True
  84 
  85     def get(self, key):
  86         # type: (Text) -> Optional[Text]
  87         """
  88         """
  89         data = self.dict()
  90 
  91         if key in data:
  92             return data[key]
  93 
  94         if self.verbose:
  95             warnings.warn("key %s not found in %s." % (key, self.dotenv_path))  # type: ignore
  96 
  97         return None
  98

 100 def get_key(dotenv_path, key_to_get):
 101     # type: (Union[Text, _PathLike], Text) -> Optional[Text]
 102     """
 103     Gets the value of a given key from the given .env
 104 
 105     If the .env path given doesn't exist, fails
 106     """
 107     return DotEnv(dotenv_path, verbose=True).get(key_to_get)

 110 @contextmanager
 111 def rewrite(path):
 112     # type: (_PathLike) -> Iterator[Tuple[IO[Text], IO[Text]]]
 113     try:
 114         with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(mode="w+", delete=False) as dest:
 115             with io.open(path) as source:
 116                 yield (source, dest)  # type: ignore
 117     except BaseException:
 118         if os.path.isfile(dest.name):
 119             os.unlink(dest.name)
 120         raise
 121     else:
 122         shutil.move(dest.name, path)
 123

 125 def set_key(dotenv_path, key_to_set, value_to_set, quote_mode="always"):
 126     # type: (_PathLike, Text, Text, Text) -> Tuple[Optional[bool], Text, Text]
 127     """
 128     Adds or Updates a key/value to the given .env
 129 
 130     If the .env path given doesn't exist, fails instead of risking creating
 131     an orphan .env somewhere in the filesystem
 132     """
 133     value_to_set = value_to_set.strip("'").strip('"')
 134     if not os.path.exists(dotenv_path):
 135         warnings.warn("can't write to %s - it doesn't exist." % dotenv_path)  # type: ignore
 136         return None, key_to_set, value_to_set
 137 
 138     if " " in value_to_set:
 139         quote_mode = "always"
 140 
 141     line_template = '{}="{}"\n' if quote_mode == "always" else '{}={}\n'
 142     line_out = line_template.format(key_to_set, value_to_set)
 143 
 144     with rewrite(dotenv_path) as (source, dest):
 145         replaced = False
 146         for mapping in parse_stream(source):
 147             if mapping.key == key_to_set:
 148                 dest.write(line_out)
 149                 replaced = True
 150             else:
 151                 dest.write(mapping.original)
 152         if not replaced:
 153             dest.write(line_out)
 154 
 155     return True, key_to_set, value_to_set
 156 
 157 
 158 def unset_key(dotenv_path, key_to_unset, quote_mode="always"):
 159     # type: (_PathLike, Text, Text) -> Tuple[Optional[bool], Text]
 160     """
 161     Removes a given key from the given .env
 162 
 163     If the .env path given doesn't exist, fails
 164     If the given key doesn't exist in the .env, fails
 165     """
 166     if not os.path.exists(dotenv_path):
 167         warnings.warn("can't delete from %s - it doesn't exist." % dotenv_path)  # type: ignore
 168         return None, key_to_unset
 169 
 170     removed = False
 171     with rewrite(dotenv_path) as (source, dest):
 172         for mapping in parse_stream(source):
 173             if mapping.key == key_to_unset:
 174                 removed = True
 175             else:
 176                 dest.write(mapping.original)
 177 
 178     if not removed:
 179         warnings.warn("key %s not removed from %s - key doesn't exist." % (key_to_unset, dotenv_path))  # type: ignore
 180         return None, key_to_unset
 181 
 182     return removed, key_to_unset

 185 def resolve_nested_variables(values):
 186     # type: (Dict[Text, Text]) -> Dict[Text, Text]
 187     def _replacement(name):
 188         # type: (Text) -> Text
 189         """
 190         get appropriate value for a variable name.
 191         first search in environ, if not found,
 192         then look into the dotenv variables
 193         """
 194         ret = os.getenv(name, new_values.get(name, ""))
 195         return ret
 196 
 197     def _re_sub_callback(match_object):
 198         # type: (Match[Text]) -> Text
 199         """
 200         From a match object gets the variable name and returns
 201         the correct replacement
 202         """
 203         return _replacement(match_object.group()[2:-1])
 204 
 205     new_values = {}
 206 
 207     for k, v in values.items():
 208         new_values[k] = __posix_variable.sub(_re_sub_callback, v)
 209 
 210     return new_values

 213 def _walk_to_root(path):
 214     # type: (Text) -> Iterator[Text]
 215     """
 216     Yield directories starting from the given directory up to the root
 217     """
 218     if not os.path.exists(path):
 219         raise IOError('Starting path not found')
 220 
 221     if os.path.isfile(path):
 222         path = os.path.dirname(path)
 223 
 224     last_dir = None
 225     current_dir = os.path.abspath(path)
 226     while last_dir != current_dir:
 227         yield current_dir
 228         parent_dir = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(current_dir, os.path.pardir))
 229         last_dir, current_dir = current_dir, parent_dir
 230

 232 def find_dotenv(filename='.env', raise_error_if_not_found=False, usecwd=False):
 233     # type: (Text, bool, bool) -> Text
 234     """
 235     Search in increasingly higher folders for the given file
 236 
 237     Returns path to the file if found, or an empty string otherwise
 238     """
 239 
 240     def _is_interactive():
 241         """ Decide whether this is running in a REPL or IPython notebook """
 242         main = __import__('__main__', None, None, fromlist=['__file__'])
 243         return not hasattr(main, '__file__')
 244 
 245     if usecwd or _is_interactive():
 246         # Should work without __file__, e.g. in REPL or IPython notebook.
 247         path = os.getcwd()
 248     else:
 249         # will work for .py files
 250         frame = sys._getframe()
 251         # find first frame that is outside of this file
 252         if PY2 and not __file__.endswith('.py'):
 253             # in Python2 __file__ extension could be .pyc or .pyo (this doesn't account
 254             # for edge case of Python compiled for non-standard extension)
 255             current_file = __file__.rsplit('.', 1)[0] + '.py'
 256         else:
 257             current_file = __file__
 258 
 259         while frame.f_code.co_filename == current_file:
 260             frame = frame.f_back
 261         frame_filename = frame.f_code.co_filename
 262         path = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(frame_filename))
 263 
 264     for dirname in _walk_to_root(path):
 265         check_path = os.path.join(dirname, filename)
 266         if os.path.isfile(check_path):
 267             return check_path
 268 
 269     if raise_error_if_not_found:
 270         raise IOError('File not found')
 271 
 272     return ''
 273

 275 def load_dotenv(dotenv_path=None, stream=None, verbose=False, override=False, **kwargs):
 276     # type: (Union[Text, _PathLike, None], Optional[_StringIO], bool, bool, Union[None, Text]) -> bool
 277     """Parse a .env file and then load all the variables found as environment variables.
 278 
 279     - *dotenv_path*: absolute or relative path to .env file.
 280     - *stream*: `StringIO` object with .env content.
 281     - *verbose*: whether to output the warnings related to missing .env file etc. Defaults to `False`.
 282     - *override*: where to override the system environment variables with the variables in `.env` file.
 283                   Defaults to `False`.
 284     """
 285     f = dotenv_path or stream or find_dotenv()
 286     return DotEnv(f, verbose=verbose, **kwargs).set_as_environment_variables(override=override)

 289 def dotenv_values(dotenv_path=None, stream=None, verbose=False, **kwargs):
 290     # type: (Union[Text, _PathLike, None], Optional[_StringIO], bool, Union[None, Text]) -> Dict[Text, Text]
 291     f = dotenv_path or stream or find_dotenv()
 292     return DotEnv(f, verbose=verbose, **kwargs).dict()
